Rating: 3
I think I may have found the 'flaw' in this recipe....I made it again but with russets adn was not nearly as good....I know it doesn't sound like rocket science, but I think to most people a potatoe is a potatoe is a potatoe. In this recipe, that isn't th4ee case. You must be sure tod use a superior quality potatoe of good flavour an texture to begin with, like a sweet red skinned or a nice yellow-fleshed variety, that will hold it's own against the leeks and integrate nicely with the other ingredients. Assure that you are using superioir potatoes to begin with, not just what you might have on hand, and it may affect your results. Good luck!

