Decided to try something different from the traditional scalloped potatoes with this year's Easter Ham (you must try the Balsamic and Dijon-Glazed ham on this site--amazing!!) and the fact that this was a 'make-ahead' dish tipped the scales in favour of this recipe, despite some reviews of failures from previous readers. My experience was that his is a verrrry tasy dish, and one that will be made often in our home. All my guests had seconds, and in some cases thirds! I modified the recipe somewhat, as I prefer a healthier diet and found this recipe a bit too high in fat. I used low-fat cream cheese, 1 cup of evaporated skim milk, 2 large eggs and 2 cups of shredded gruyere. It was still delicious, and I didn't feel guilty about having seconds!!

